:Licence: GPLv2+
:Status: beta
:Tags: rpi


Use HD44780 LCD Module to monitor Raspberry Pi.
For now - display informations from MPD daemon, load.

Building
========
Requirements:
 * GoLang 1.4, 1.5 (v1.4 on rpi don't handle signals)
 * Libraries (go get):

   * gompd (http://github.com/turbowookie/gompd/mpd)
   * go-rpio (https://github.com/stianeikeland/go-rpio)

Building:
 * go get .
 * `make` or `make build_pi` for RaspberryPi

Running
=======

Local (without lcd/gpio): ./rpilcd -console=true

With gpio (on RPI) - require sudo.

Options
-------
 * `-mpdHost=pi:6600` - address:port mpd daemon
 * `-console`' - display messages on console instead of lcd
 * `-startService=true` - start local tcp server for urgent messages
 * `-serviceAddr=localhost:8681` - local tcp server address

Urgent messages
---------------
Send text or json-structure to localhost:8681 (or other configured by
--ws_addr param) some text; ie:
::

     echo 'test' | nc localhost 8681


JSON structure:
::

   {
      "Text": "some tekst to display",
      "Timeout": 5,
      "PutOnTop": true
   }


